+
+### System Architecture Summary
+
+**Pattern:** Event-Driven with Adapter Pattern
+
+```
+Domain Services (OrderService, UserService)
+    ‚îÇ emit events
+    ‚ñº
+EventBus
+    ‚îÇ delivers to subscribers
+    ‚ñº
+NotificationService
+    ‚îÇ checks PreferencesService (opt-out)
+    ‚îÇ creates NotificationPayload
+    ‚îÇ dispatches to adapter
+    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ EmailAdapter (HTML templates, pluggable transport)
+    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ SmsAdapter (E.164 validation, 160-char truncation, pluggable transport)
+    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ WebhookAdapter (JSON POST, URL validation, pluggable transport)
+    ‚îÇ
+    ‚ñº
+NotificationHistoryService ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ NotificationLogRepository
+    (audit log with multi-filter queries)
+```
+
+**Key components (24 source files, ~1,140 lines):**
+- **Models:** `notification.ts`, `notification-log.ts`, `user-preferences.ts`, `order.ts`, `user.ts`
+- **Adapters:** `notification.adapter.ts` (interface), `email.adapter.ts`, `webhook.adapter.ts`, `sms.adapter.ts` ‚Äî all follow identical transport/config/convenience-method pattern
+- **Services:** `notification.service.ts` (orchestrator), `notification-history.service.ts` (audit), `preferences.service.ts` (opt-out), `order.service.ts`, `user.service.ts`
+- **Repositories:** `base.repository.ts`, `notification-log.repository.ts`, `preferences.repository.ts`, `order.repository.ts`, `user.repository.ts`
+- **Validators:** `order.validator.ts`, `user.validator.ts`, `preferences.validator.ts` ‚Äî pure functions, no side effects
+- **Events:** `event-bus.ts`, `event-types.ts`
+- **Utils:** `database.ts`, `logger.ts`, `pagination.ts`
+
+**Per-channel user preferences:**
+- Email: enabled, frequency (immediate/daily_digest/weekly_digest/none), subscribedCategories
+- SMS: enabled, subscribedCategories
+- Webhook: enabled, subscribedCategories, optional URL
+- Unknown channels (e.g., `in_app`) default to allowing delivery
+
+### Known Limitations
+
+1. **`handleOrderStatusChanged` uses `order.userId` as recipient** ‚Äî `OrderStatusChangedEvent` lacks a `User` object, so the recipient is a user ID (e.g., `'user-1'`), not an email address. The email adapter rejects this. Fix: add `user` field to the event or look up user email from a repository.
+
+2. **`user:created` and `user:updated` events have no notification handlers** ‚Äî `UserService` emits these events and notification types `'welcome'` and `'account_updated'` exist with email templates, but `NotificationService.registerEventHandlers()` doesn't subscribe to them. The email adapter templates for these types are unreachable.
+
+3. **`in_app` channel is defined in the type system but has no adapter** ‚Äî `NotificationChannel` includes `'in_app'` as a future extension point, but there is no `InAppAdapter`. Notifications sent to this channel are recorded as "sent" without actual delivery (no-adapter fallback behavior).
+
+4. **All adapters use in-memory transports by default** ‚Äî production deployment requires injecting real transports (SMTP/SES for email, HTTP client for webhook, Twilio/SNS for SMS).
+
+5. **No retry mechanism** ‚Äî failed notifications are logged but not retried. The history service records the failure status for manual review.
+
